-- Simor Says Looser Hungarian Monetary Policy Would Be 'Hard to Justify'
-- B y   B a l a z s   P e n z
-- 2010-10-14T06:34:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/simor-says-looser-hungarian-monetary-policy-would-be-hard-to-justify-.html
Hungarian central bank President
Andras Simor said “it would be difficult to justify a looser
monetary policy than the current one” because the aim of policy
makers is to reach price stability.  The central bank also takes into account Hungary’s risk
assessment, which worsened in the past three or four months,
Simor said in an interview with the Budapest-based weekly HVG,
published today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  